Oil prices dropped despite Hurricane Rita approaching the Gulf of Mexico, as OPEC promised increased crude supply if needed.
New York's main contract fell to $66.30 per barrel, while London's Brent North Sea crude dropped to $64.32.
Hurricane Rita strengthened to a category two storm with winds of 160 km/h, prompting flight suspensions and evacuations.
Texas prepared for evacuations as Rita threatened the Gulf Coast, following the devastation of Hurricane Katrina.
Louisiana declared a state of emergency, urging residents to evacuate as Rita posed a significant threat.
Galveston ordered a mandatory evacuation, with Rita expected to intensify to a Category 4
